values:
"my little sister and her friend" ... and HER friend.  Low blow.  
and I'm moving on.

I think yes.  I just returned from an amazing five day river rafting trip on the deschuttes river.  I learned how to guide and I might take guiding as a summer job next year.  dum dee dum.  The trip was amazing, I went with LEAD and they are such a family of friends.  It was incredible, no drama, just enjoyment and laughter.  Oh and the day before I left Talon kissed me... we'll see how that works out, it would be nice if it did work out.  LEAD invited me to go on the tuesday group as well, but COUNTRY FAIR.  Oh man I'm excited.  I'm going to Talon's barbecue tonight, I haven't seen him since sunday night.  I feel like a little girl, this is different.  And so life goes.

My life is being almost too amazing.  Last night was summer solstice and the full moon.  But no, that is not enough.  I had an awesome time just hanging out at this party and was one of the last to leave.  It was a small relaxed party where you actually talk to people, my favorite.  So I was about to walk home and I'm just talking with the host when he mentions that he is unusually comfortable around me, which surprised me because it felt as though he wasn't even that comfortable around me.  At any rate some how the conversation led to him awkwardly asking for a massage, so of course I give him one.  He is uptight and won't relax and we are just conversing as I try and coax him to relax a bit.  As the night wore on he slowly grew more and more comfortable and relaxed and we made an incredible connection.  We spent 5 hours, just the two of us, messaging and cuddling and talking.  AND THAT'S ALL!!!  It was incredible, there was no attempt to kiss, no sexual energy, just complete comfort. That's what he kept repeating too, "I've never felt this comfortable around anyone", "you are an incredibly comfortable person", over and over again he would say the word comfort.  Comfort would be the theme of the night, indescribable comfort.

So this past weekend was not only my Birthday, but it was the rugby Pacific Coast Territorial Tournament.  Which means the Loggers (Oregon-Washington select side team), which I am on, played the Griffens (California select side team).  We arrived on Friday (my birthday) and that night that the coach (who is a scout for the national team) had selected me to be the Captain of the Loggers.  Saturday we did some scrimmaging and I did not play my best because I was feeling insecure and our team was not playing individually because we had never played together before.  That night the coaches gave us a pep talk on what we could do better.  I also talked to the coach separately and she told me that she chose me as captain because in the All-Star game I was intimidating and a threat.  On Saturday I was not a threat and she wanted me to regain that intimidation factor on Sunday for the championship game.

Sunday I was in awe.  We played the most beautiful game of Rugby I had ever played.  I completely stepped up my game, I did everything the coaches suggested and more.   I poached the ball again and again. I got to play 8-Man the whole game and we did some amazing back row plays.  Our team played flawlessly together, it seemed as though we were reading each others minds. I was completely honored to be playing with every single person on my team.

At the awards ceremony three awards were given out, best back, best forward, and MVP.  I didn't think I would win any awards.  They announced best back and best forward and began introducing the MVP awards by saying: "this award we had to split between two players because you could hardly tell the difference between them on the field, in fact they're practically twins".  At this point my jaw is totally dropped and my whole team is hitting Marie and I.  "Number 7 and Number 8 from Loggers: Marie Rochat and Maya Rios".  I just about shit a brick.  That was the perfect end to and amazing weekend.

For those of you who don't know Marie is my evil Rugby twin who is on the National team and has already broken two world records in dead-lifting, to be placed at the same level as her in rugby is very honoring!  It was so perfect!

To top it all off, the coach comes up to me, hands me the team trophy for winning the tournament and says "congratulations Maya on leading your team to victory".  At this point I stupidly mumble "what?" and she clarifies "The trophy is yours to take home"

Sorry for just dictating my entire weekend in detail but it was one of the best weekends of my life.  I almost cried and my coach from South Eugene did actually cry.  I was chosen to be captain and all of the players on my team expressed that they loved me as captain and I won Most Valuable Player for the entire west coast with my evil rugby twin, Marie!

I puked for the first time in my life!! Three times to be precise.  I was at the Folk Live Festival in Seattle and I ate an elephant ear.  I think I got food poisoning.  It was also the first day of my period so at first I thought it was awful cramps, but then the pain got so severe that I cried.  Thats right folks I, Maya Rios, cried from physical pain.  It was pretty intense.  So I called my grandparents to come pick me up (once again showing exactly how much pain I was in) and I was waiting for grandpa at the corner of fifth and Harrison in Seattle.  For those of you who don't know Fifth and Harrison is the corner that the space needle is on and it is 2:30pm and the folk live festival is going on at the Seattle Center, there was a lot of people to say the least.  So there I am waiting on this busy street corner, doubled over from pain, when all of a sudden I find myself projecting vomit.  I threw up forcefully three times and then I heard a round of applause.  I look up to see a tour bus full of people clapping and cheering for me.  I then turn around to see an M&M man stationed at the corner chuckling to himself.  Everyone is staring at me with that look that obviously says "man, she's that drunk ALREADY?".  After that I felt much better, though not wholly so.  Oh and I got to hang out on the corner for another 15 min with the M&M man as my companion.

So, what a story for the first time ever puking in your life, I know Cath and Nicole have to be proud!

so my picture is in the daily emrald from when I was playing in the alumni vs. ducks game!  KICK ASS.  Also loggers clinic this saturday is going to kick ass as well, and then I get to spend the weekend with my grandparents!  = )  I am super excited!

and it crossed my mind as I was sitting there with FORTY-FIVE minutes left wondering if it was a bad thing I finished the essay portion in HALF the time alloted...

so what happens after Maya has been sitting for 40 minutes stressing out and not being able to move from my seat?
That's right, I write poetry about how much I hate AP tests.

and for your amusement:

Nerves... Pound through me
I just can't stop shaking my knee
A years worth of time
Amounts to three hours of stress
Bitter as a lime, I feel like a mess
My brain and my gut have been blended together
As the sound of pens scribbling goes on forever
A single test meant to judge your intellect
Based on the details you've managed to recollect.



oh man, you know you like it.

so yeah traumatizing times when a bunch of stoner teenage boys ambush your IM and talk to your friends that you haven't talked to in a while, so they don't know that your not ACTUALLY an acid head and the mother of twins...

Sorry about that liz, definitely not Maya who was speaking, except for all the bye's

Your Birthdate: June 10
Your birth on the 10th day of the month adds a tone of independence and extra energy to your life. The number 1 energy suggest more executive ability and leadership qualities than you path may have indicated. A birthday on the 10th of any month gives greater will power and self-confidence, and very often a rather original approach. This 1 energy may diminish your ability and desire to handle details, preferring instead to paint with a broad brush. You are sensitive, but your feeling stay somewhat repressed. You have a compelling manner that can be dominating in many situations.
What Does Your Birth Date Mean?
this actually discribes me fairly acurately, I was impressed.

Luke turned 18, I didn't even call to wish him happy birthday. I think I'm a bad girlfriend. Luke cleaned my room the other day after I had to leave at 6am. He is the ultimate sweetheart.
The U19 sectionals game was AWESOME.  I think I have a good chance of making loggers and I was nominated Captain and was the only person on my team to play the full 60 minutes when we weren't supposed to play more than 40... I also received so many complements, I swear I'm floating.  OOOO I have the prettiest bruise, it's a full cleat mark (six stud marks) that is to the point that each stud mark has the yellow bruise in the center.  I love all of the rugby boys.  They make me smile and feel loved.

Luckily I finally figured out my transcript and I will be taking the Rachel Carson CAM next year as well as AP Psychology.

DAN AND ERIK SHOWED UP AT MY HOUSE TODAY.  They came home a month early from Hawaii and it was so incredible to see them!  I missed those kids a ridiculous amount.  In fact I was so excited I ran head first into a door and now I have an enormous lump on my head.  Slickness to the max!

also hooray for syllabus burning bonfire parties

pssshhhh I don't talk on the phone!

My poli sci class is INCREDIBLE!!!!  I don't even know where to begin, I have had 2 classes and already learned so much and the entire class is discussion and no bullshit, Ken is a phenomenal discussion leader.

so I haven't talked to luke all week, hooray for phone tag and no way to leave messages, I feel like a horrible person.  On the bright side, tunnel tag in mudpits are WICKED fun, and I have been loving my vocabulary recently.  Today I said "down low" completely normally in conversation FLIPPIN SWEET!

I was looking back through my year book from Conserve school and practically everyone mentioned that I was very unique, not necessarily in a positive way but apparently I stand out...  It confuses me, when I see others that stand out in a crowd I can point out why it is they stand out.  I don't do anything attention grabbing the way someone who I would characterize as standing out would.  Also we are all completely unique and our own persons entirely separate from anyone else, what makes me even more to that extreme? It is so odd to try and look at oneself from others point of view.
so it's definitely hailing outside right now and not just freezing rain, there is no rain involved and I am talking pea sized... Yeah I have no idea either.

"If you want to learn to love better, you should start with 
a friend who you hate"
              -A six year old when asked to describe what love is

I promise I will get back about all of the other people I love at some point Kara you know I love you like wow so I hope you're not offended I paused at you, in fact you should take it as compliment that I had faith that you would know how much you rock the world.  

So this is me procrastinating, shocker I know.  Three final papers and a physics final tomorrow.  So anyone else ever notice how beautiful boys are?  For some reason recently I have been noticing how beautiful everyone is, maybe it's the weather.

I can't wait till tomorrow evening, I will be done with all finals and I will be at a Decemberists concert.  Then this saturday my HALEY is coming to town, so pumped we are going to have a blast.  On the 23rd DAVI is coming into town as well, and my excitement is needless to say.  Over break I am going to visit LUKE at aprovecho, wow it's only Tuesday, I have to wait till friday to see him again, hooray for peter pan.  Also last weekend of break it looks like I will be going to Seattle for a frisbee tourny, I also have some kids who want me to join the U of O frisbee team which would be a blast.  Also I am going to try and do a coast trip with Haley and Davi however I really don't want to go on Britt's trip as much as I love her the energy will be horrible with all the people going.  My rugby team rules everyone, but we don't have enough players which is a bit of a bummer, but we are kicking major ass.

HOW I LOVE BEING ALIVE

Josh.  Josh you have amazing energy, you are one of the few people who can empathize with my extrovertedness.  You have been a close friend of my families for a while now.  You have always been there to support us and listen to our bullshit.  You have wonderful wacky ideas and make everyone feel welcome and worthwhile.  I unfortunately have not seen or talked to you in quite a while which makes me have Josh withdrawls from time to time.  I miss your upbeat energy that has a way of infecting areas with positivity and laughter.  I love how you listen as fervently (if not more so) to six-year-olds as you do adults and can bring out the intelligence in everyone around you.  You are an amazing friend who I always know will be there to hug or cry to and you bring so much warmth into peoples heart.  Though most of all I love your ability to play with everyone and anyone with out a stop.

Helen you will always be my ass-kicking fiddling buddy!  I'm so glad we became friends even if you did hate me for 6th and part of 7th grade = P.  All I can say is "what does tapioca look like if you put it under a microscope".  I was a corrupting little bitch and you still shared your jellies with me, that means a lot.  It was also fun coming back to visit to have you now corrupt me.  What happened to innocent Helen?  It's awesome.  But back to why I friggen love you to pieces.  I love you for your power girl.  You have so much energy and drive that when you direct it you are able to achieve what you set out for, it is so amazingly beautiful.  Once you get into something, no matter what it is, you go all the way.  This is true when it comes to friends as well.  Once we became friends I was able to see that you would back up your friends and support them in whatever their endeavors were until the very end.  You are one of those people I would choose to have by my side in a fight, and you would be there.  You might be a third the size of the guys we would fight but you would take them out if it came down to that.  Helen I guess I'm just trying to say that you are awesome and hardcore in every sense of the words.  I really hope you are having a good time all the way across the world and I had better see you soon!

Max, I just have to reiterate that you are the happiest depressed kid I have ever met.  Every time I see you I can't help but grin and I compulsively get the urge to give you a huge hug.  You just dance to your own tune and your dance is beautiful.  That's all I can say, everything about is beautiful, you are a truly beautiful person.  Your are all around just a good person, you are kind and helpful and loving and give wonderful hugs.  You just bring your own perspective and mindset to any and every situation and have this ability that forces everyone who talks to you to love you.  You are also an amazing listener.  You have not only sat through my rants but I always know you actually hear what I say as though it is worthwhile.  I love you so much Max and I wish I saw more of you, my Max time is definitely way too sporadic.

If I'd like.... 
Well, I would like to.  

Darcy you have the most interesting combination of cockyness and insecurity.  I love you; I honestly can say, always have always will.  You just allow yourself to go with it, doesn't matter what "it" is, you go with it.  You encourage others to give in to their own urges as well.  It's so wonderful.  You truly enjoy yourself doing whatever activity you choose to do and are always willing to have others due what suits them.  I have never heard a judgemental word out of your mouth.  You definitely have opinions though and stick to what you believe and care for.  You are also always willing to share your knowledge and opinions with out fear or care of being judged by others.  You have your opinions, other people have theirs, they can live by their opinions and you live by yours.  There are so few people who truly actually are that way.  You are one of them.  Darcy, I could go on all day trying to explain what it is that I like and love and am attracted to about you, though I doubt I could truly put it into words and certaintly could not narrow it down to one aspect of you.  Though I suppose what I am trying to say is one of the things I appreciate about you the most is your off-beat way of being at peace with who you are and who other people are.

SALLY!  Gah I LOVE YOU!  You have so much love in you, I don't know how you fit it in.  Love for everyone in everyform no matter how much they hurt you.  I would have to say that what I miss most about you is your smile and your hug.  With your comfort no one could truly doubt themselves.  I have watched and experienced you pulling so many people through their own shit even though you still have your own to deal with.  You are a true friend.  Sometimes I think to myself "where is Sally, and why is she no longer in my daily life?".  This of course makes me sad only for long enough for me to remember the many times I have tortured you by sitting on you when you had to pee, and then I just giggle and remember how much bullshit of mine you put up with and in turn how much I love you and your own unique way of appreciating anyone and everyone for who they are.  I love you Sally.

Gosh chica, I don't even know what to say.  You have always been a true friend to me, even when you don't understand a word I am saying or I don't understand a word you are saying.  Since sixth grade everytime I see you I am greeted with love and friendship.  You are always there to tell me the truth and make me see what's going on in the world.  You have amazing perspective and always see things as they are, you have kept me in line more times than I can remember.  You were the one who was a friend even when I was a complete bitch.  I love you so much Haley, you are truly a "cool" person, because you are kind to everyone and don't put up with bullshit while still remaining calm and not tweaking out on anyone.  I have so much respect for you and I always manage to laugh when your around, I can not wait till you come to Oregon and I can share this life that I have with you.

Rose is an amazingly kind, genuine friend.  The first time I met Rose she was game for anything.  Hey we are going to play "soccer" in the gym and beat the crap out of each other, wanna come?  And of course she comes and has an amazing time with us (one of the few prosbies to actually converse with us).  I remember after talking with her and getting to know Rose on the prospective student day I wrote the Admin. and told them they had no choice but to admit her.  So luckily for the Admin. Rose came to Conserve school the next year.  Seeing as we now lived together we just bonded more and more as the year went on.  Rose was always game to laugh and rock out with me and put up with my shenanigans whenever I needed a release.  She always greets me with a smile and a hug and was definitely a big factor in keeping me sane for that year in the frigid north.  I miss you so much Rose I can't even describe and it is mandatory that you come visit me, you will love Oregon I promise.  I also definitely have not received my Rose quota recently, so we need to talk more often!

I played in my first rugby game ever yesterday.  It was amazing.  We technically had to forfiet due to low numbers, but we played and won anyway.  I played 8-man which is a loose forward and I scored two tris and assisted two others.  I was astonished at how incredibley nice everyone who plays rugby is.  Our team kicked it with the other team after the game and every single person on both teams were just incredible people.  So many people including of course my coach, players on the other team, the ref, and the boys on our boys team gave me some of the best compliments I've ever recieved for a sport.  My friend Luke watched the game and told me afterwards that "I don't let my body limit myself"  and one of the girls on the other team was talking to one of my teamates and was saying "one of your girls tackles hard!  I mean it sucks for me, but damn she's awesome!"  and then as I walked by she pointed at me and said "her, that's the one".  So yeah I'm just a bit pumped and rugby is the best sport EVER!

Monkey just dropped me off after playing capture the flag.  I'm tempted to say that the best part of my week is the half-hour car ride after capture the flag in which I have the most amazing, inspiring conversations with him.  Every time, even though I live about 6 blocks from where we play capture the flag he takes mike home first who lives in springfield so we have this time to converse.  Monk also asked me to write him a recommendation because he wants to get his masters in education and is applying to the U of O.  I suppose that meant a lot to me that he wanted me to write his recommendation.

So I just got back from a YA/youth AR/AO con.  In other words it was an Anti-racism/Anti-oppression conference with adults, young adults, and youth.  It was really amazing.  Mike (The one who wants me to play bass in his band) gave me a ride to the U of O today.  That was really awesome because it gave me time to finish my homework.  Ethan who is in both my Systems Thinking and Solar and renewable energies class came up to me and chatted with me, he's super awesome.  I am stupid and play frisbee at night when FROST IS FORMING ON THE FIELD.  I've been feeling sick recently and I'm considering dropping Law and American Society as much as I love that class.  I am going on the Rachel Carson trip down to THE REDWOODS in california this coming weekend.  I am ridiculously excited, though Tim will have to proctor my PHYS 162 midterm while we are down there.

I just saw a picture of Sam Monfort, my best friend up until 2nd grade when he started calling me "Maya Papaya" cuz I had cooties.  I wouldn't have even recognized it as him except that the picture was labeled, wow time is crazy.
so apparently Ambrea and Hanna Williams are in prison in Ecuador because someone planted cocaine in their backpacks.... random, and a bit hilarious in a horrible sort of way.
I love digital cameras and 18th birthdays.  What's this I hear about my brother hitchiking across the country and why don't I know about it?

hooray for frisbee and feeling loved.  I have a nosebleed randomly and I can't wait till the play is over oh man my throat hurts from talking.  I randomly got invited to go play frisbee with these kids the practice at the same time same place as the frat frisbee team and I remember going to the frat house practice and noticing the other team on the neighboring field and seeing how much awesome fun they had.  So definitely it was the people I just played with the other night and it was ridiculously fun.  I love making new friends especially when two of your closest friends are about the leave for Hawaii (coughcough*DanandErik*coughcough) anyhow that's my rant.

So we were just kickin it and Erik for some reason is describing to us his "ideal girl".  He didn't know it when he was telling us but he perfectly described me...
I suppose I'm flattered a bit, but I hope that nothing like that happens ever again
My play goes up this friday!  Everyone should come see it and here me talk because I'm just that interesting!

I don't know why I keep doing these.
You are water. You're not really organic; you're
neither acidic nor basic, yet you're an acid
and a base at the same time. You're strong
willed and opinionated, but relaxed and ready
to flow. So while you often seem worthless,
without you, everything would just not work.
People should definitely drink more of you
every day.

Which Biological Molecule Are You?
brought to you by Quizilla

You're Costa Rica!
You're about as peaceful as anyone on the planet, a real dyed-in-the-wool pacifist.  And why not?  No one really poses much of a threat to you and everything seems to work out, no matter how much violence and insanity rages all around you.  So you relax and appreciate nature and culture while the rest of the world carries on their petty disagreements.  If only everyone could follow your example...
Take the Country Quiz at the Blue Pyramid

and they keep telling me I'm not a pacifist.

You're Oregon!
When people talk about peace in the valley, they often think of you. After all, you've inspired countless people to traverse rough terrain in search of you and even think about you when playing popular computer games. Are you really up to all the hype or are you all wet? You take shelter from the storm beneath trees, felled by either loggers or beavers. If you were a shade of pink, it would be salmon.
Take the State Quiz at the Blue Pyramid.

I guess I moved to the right place...

I just returned from backpacking with Sarah, Gia, and Rosie.  Ri-cock-ulus times, lots and lots of good memories from three short days.  Hooray for prancing park rangers at 2:30am.  I don't think I can eat again for a couple days.  Well I am returning to Eugene tomorrow.

yeah, I'm a dork, it's cool.  So I am currently in Arlington VA, my cousin who I haven't seen since I was six is randomly here which is awesome.  Arturo I super cool so it's great to see him again and it just reinforces the idea that I really need to visit Puerto Rico again.  So now I am torn, should I go to chicago or Puerto Rico for spring break?  Other than that I am just reminded as to why I left arlington, well I do see some things that I miss dearly but I am definitley aware of the negative aspects this trip.  Seeing family is always good, I don't know how they can all be so awesome, Rios (my cousin Paul's baby) is such an incredible kid and of course my entire family has to give me shit about being a tree-hugging hippie and insane because I only eat raw food.    Davi is halfway considering going to the U of O next year which would be so awesome because I miss you ridiculus amounts.  Well I am enjoying my break, but I have not done any of the insane amount of work I have to do this break.

Hooray for hallway marco polo, pass the Maya, and yoga with Eric.  Tempermental boys drive me crazy. The play's coming together, but I really really need to memorize my monologues.  Free clothes are always good.  Today was an awesome day because I felt awesome.


Today however was interesting, I wasn't feeling particularly good about myself but then I overheard a conversation two of my lab partners in AP/IB Bio were having about how smart I am, and then a girl at school said I always look so cute and a third party stopped me in the halls to ask me what grade I was in and when I asked why they wanted to know their response was because they thought I was hot...  I guess I can't help but get excited to randomly get complements
By the way I will be in Arlington on december 20th... and I lost my phone so leave a comment or call Davi or something if you want to hang out (which I know you do)

I just returned from playing frisbee at the U of O and I wasn't terrible.  I was even invited back!  I am excited because practically everyone there was better than me but not so much that I never got the disc and it wasn't competetive enough for people to get angry when I fucked up, however most people were better than me so I played up to their level and I was constantly learning how to play better.  Other than that it was great because all of the people there were really awesome despite the fact that every single one of them besides Sebastian were frat boys.
